3 F. Notwithstanding the provisions of the Oklahoma Surplus
4 Property Act, the Oklahoma Highway Patrol may, pursuant to rules
5 promulgated by the Director of the Office of Management and
6 Enterprise Services, donate surplus Oklahoma Highway Patrol vehicles
7 driven over ninety thousand (90,000) miles to any law enforcement
8 agency of any political subdivision of the State of Oklahoma in a
9 county with a population of no more than one hundred thousand
10 (100,000) residents. The use of such donated vehicles shall be
11 limited to valid and authorized law enforcement efforts by the
12 receiving agency.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
